The paper deals with the problem of partitioning a graph into equal-sized parts, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory. This problem is closely related to several other well-studied problems in computer science, such as cluster vertex deletion number, feedback vertex set, and vertex cover number. Therefore, the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of arXiv CS, including Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Among these, cs.DM and cs.DS are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with combinatorial and algorithmic aspects of graph partitioning.
